{"event_id":"published:plan:01kn0yaqr4ktj8ey63r1r3n79q:22","kind":"node_updated","plan_id":"plan:01kn0yaqr4ktj8ey63r1r3n79q","node_id":"coord-task:01kn0yb9zz75x9sngz7eppvvt8","payload":{"type":"node","node":{"id":"coord-task:01kn0yb9zz75x9sngz7eppvvt8","plan_id":"plan:01kn0yaqr4ktj8ey63r1r3n79q","kind":"Edit","title":"Instrument and rank hidden repo-scale persistence work","summary":"Audited narrow refresh and mutation paths for hidden repo-scale work. The highest-priority hotspots are: sqlite index persistence still spending most time in global side-data writes rather than file-state upserts; outcome and episodic snapshot saves reloading whole event logs inside hot transactions; projection delta application issuing thousands of co-change upserts plus a global prune on tiny refreshes; targeted index persistence still rewriting derived-edge and finalize state repo-wide. The audit also identified full-snapshot history replacement and full-table inference reconciliation as broader patterns that should stay in scope while fixing the hot paths.","status":"Completed","bindings":{"anchors":[{"File":263},{"File":74}],"concept_handles":[],"artifact_refs":[],"memory_refs":[],"outcome_refs":[]},"acceptance":[{"label":"The dominant repo-scale costs on narrow refresh and mutation paths are identified with concrete code anchors and runtime evidence.","anchors":[],"required_checks":[],"evidence_policy":"Any"}],"validation_refs":[],"is_abstract":false,"assignee":null,"base_revision":{"graph_version":1152,"git_commit":null},"priority":null,"tags":[],"metadata":null}}}
